Hey Tajiyo, an intruder just came this way.

271
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:11,560
Which way did he go?

272
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:13,140
Eh? I didn't see anyone.

273
00:19:13,140 --> 00:19:15,410
Maybe you were imagining things.

274
00:19:15,410 --> 00:19:16,530
Keep searching!

275
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:18,740
He must be somewhere on this ship!

276
00:19:18,740 --> 00:19:20,130
Keep searching!

277
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:27,470
Bastard...

278
00:19:27,470 --> 00:19:30,350
You got some kind of grudge against me?

279
00:19:30,350 --> 00:19:31,680
I'm sorry.

280
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:34,220
That face doesn't look like it's sorry.

281
00:19:34,220 --> 00:19:35,770
I'm saying I'm sorry.

282
00:19:35,770 --> 00:19:37,170
I'll kick you off this ship, jackass...

283
00:19:38,840 --> 00:19:39,750
What's wrong, Luffy?

284
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:44,040
Ah! You damaged the Going Merry again!

285
00:19:44,040 --> 00:19:46,300
Oh, Usopp, Nami, sorry.

286
00:19:46,300 --> 00:19:49,010
I got spotted by the Marines, so we had to rush back.

287
00:19:49,810 --> 00:19:50,780
WHAT!?

288
00:19:50,780 --> 00:19:53,070
W-Wait, what do you mean by that!?

289
00:19:53,070 --> 00:19:56,460
This ship was a gift from Kaya!

290
00:19:56,460 --> 00:19:58,730
How many times do I have to tell you that!?

291
00:19:58,730 --> 00:19:59,740
We have to get going!

292
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:01,990
Usopp, Sanji-kun! Let's set sail!

293
00:20:01,990 --> 00:20:04,420
Right away, Nami-san! 

294
00:20:04,420 --> 00:20:05,960
My body won't move...

295
00:20:21,180 --> 00:20:22,180
Set the places.

296
00:20:22,180 --> 00:20:23,220
Yes, Sir!

297
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:40,670
Now, please help yourselves.

298
00:20:53,030 --> 00:20:54,870
Oh, this is pretty good.

299
00:20:54,870 --> 00:20:58,180
The spice's aroma is spreading through my mouth!

300
00:20:58,180 --> 00:21:00,580
And this meat is so tender!

301
00:21:00,580 --> 00:21:02,550
Seconds, please!

302
00:21:03,730 --> 00:21:04,610
Tajiyo.

303
00:21:04,610 --> 00:21:06,130
Yes, Chef.

304
00:21:06,130 --> 00:21:09,630
Don't forget to wash the dishes later.

305
00:21:10,550 --> 00:21:11,450
Aye, Sir.

306
00:21:23,470 --> 00:21:24,380
Sanji-san...

307
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,730
I think it exists too.

308
00:21:29,730 --> 00:21:31,220
All Blue!

309
00:21:42,300 --> 00:21:44,460
I'll never give up!

310
00:21:44,460 --> 00:21:48,470
And someday, I'll be an even better cook than you!

311
00:21:54,560 --> 00:22:02,740
Ah, as I look beyond the endless sky

312
00:22:02,740 --> 00:22:13,330
I begin to imagine a tomorrow that I'll have some day

313
00:22:21,220 --> 00:22:28,640
There were days when I feel like I'd lose to myself

314
00:22:28,640 --> 00:22:37,070
But there was a warm place I could always go

315
00:22:37,070 --> 00:22:43,180
People I could be proud of were always there

316
00:22:43,180 --> 00:22:54,120
Placing hands upon my back and pushing me onwards

317
00:22:54,120 --> 00:23:02,680
Ah, the stars are streaming down beneath the sky

318
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:04,800
This only happens once...

